feat(site): abbr tooltips + SCORE2/HFA-ICOS DOI links

Hover definitions
- Added abbr title tooltips to the acronyms that carry most weight in
  the scientific paragraphs: ADT, GnRH, ARSI, MACE, OMOP-CDM, GDPR,
  APPI. Hovering the term shows its expansion and a short definition.
- Applied across why.p1, why.p2, how.p1, and how.endpoint, in EN / JA
  / FR. Titles are localised per language.
- how.endpoint markup switched from data-i18n to data-i18n-html so the
  new abbr + anchor tags render.
- i18n.js sanitiser extended to allow abbr elements with the title
  attribute (still blocks any other tag).
- CSS: abbr title now renders with a dotted underline and cursor help,
  and the underline turns accent-blue on hover for discoverability.

References
- SCORE2 now links to Eur Heart J 2021 (doi.org/10.1093/eurheartj/ehab309).
- HFA-ICOS now links to Lyon et al., Eur J Heart Fail 2020
  (doi.org/10.1002/ejhf.1920).
- HERO reference on how.endpoint also linked via DOI so the mention
  in the endpoint tile is navigable.

i18n parity preserved at 235 keys.
